- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the optimization of power allocation in a communication system with energy harvesting nodes. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on two-hop relaying in a communication network. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the optimization of a system with energy harvesting devices. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) could be a relevant category as the paper considers the problem of relaying in a multi-agent communication network. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with the optimization of power allocation in a distributed communication system.
